description: This course will provide a foundation for students to develop their knowledge base on the incidence, causal factors and medical management of multiple pregnancy and preterm birth. They will also develop a wider knowledge of the complexities of caring for vulnerable newborn infants and their parents.
prerequisites: NURS1001, NURS1002, NURS1003, NURS1004, MIDW1005, MIDW1006, MIDW1007,MIDW1008,MIDW2001, MIDW2002, MIDW2004, MIDW2005
restricted: Bachelor of Midwifery or BN/BMid. students
